    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Propolis Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is propolis and how does it support immunity?</summary><p>Propolis is a resinous bee-produced substance containing 300+ bioactive compounds (CAPE, flavonoids). Bees use it to sterilize hives. For humans: antibacterial, antiviral, antifungal, anti-inflammatory, and immunomodulatory. Clinical trials show reduced cold frequency (63%) and duration.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much propolis should I take daily?</summary><p>200-300mg daily for prevention. 300-500mg for acute cold-season support. Look for standardization to flavonoid content or CAPE concentration. Brazilian green propolis and European propolis have the most clinical evidence. Take with food.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Is propolis safe for people with bee allergies?</summary><p>No. Avoid propolis if allergic to bee stings, honey, royal jelly, or bee pollen. Cross-reactivity is possible. Reactions range from mild rash to anaphylaxis. If you have multiple allergies or anaphylaxis history, consult an allergist before use.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is the difference between propolis types?</summary><p>Brazilian green propolis (most studied, rich in artepillin C + CAPE), European propolis (flavonoid-rich, strong antibacterial), Red propolis (isoflavonoid-rich, strong antioxidant). Composition depends on geographic origin and plant sources bees forage from.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take propolis every day during cold season?</summary><p>Yes. Clinical trials support daily use for 3+ months during cold season. Works through direct antimicrobial activity + immune cell activation. Start in October (before peak season) and continue through April. Both seasonal and year-round use are considered safe.</p></details>

